<subSubSection id="91F4650B280EFFA7FF4CFB75FB71FA96" pageId="30" pageNumber="459" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D9513680280EFFA7FF4CFB75FB71FA96" blockId="30.[151,1437,151,1293]" pageId="30" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA92280EFFA7FF4CFB75FE89FB5F" bold="true" box="[199,332,1194,1220]" pageId="30" pageNumber="459">Discussion.</emphasis>
Willis Wirth wrote “ 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D03280EFFA7FDB0FB74FD24FB5E" box="[571,737,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spicata">Bezzia spicata</taxonomicName>
D. &amp; T.” on the locality labels of the 
<typeStatus id="06558822280EFFA7FB12FB74FB3EFB5E" box="[1177,1275,1195,1221]" pageId="30" pageNumber="459">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="06558822280EFFA7FABEFB74FA5CFB5E" box="[1333,1433,1195,1221]" pageId="30" pageNumber="459">paratype</typeStatus>
. However, based on their elongate gonostylus with a very long outer prong, moderately slender parameres, and different leg banding patterns, they are clearly not members of that previously described species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
